WEBVTT

00:02.700 --> 00:04.300
I had a great dream
last night.

00:04.800 --> 00:06.000
Really?
Yeah.

00:06.000 --> 00:08.300
I dreamed I got locked
in a house made of donuts

00:08.300 --> 00:10.300
and I had to eat my way out.

00:11.700 --> 00:12.600
Interesting.

00:12.600 --> 00:16.600
I had a similar dream,
only no house and no donuts.

00:18.400 --> 00:19.200
Morning.

00:19.200 --> 00:20.300
Morning.
Morning.

00:20.800 --> 00:21.800
So, uh...

00:21.800 --> 00:23.200
how'd everybody sleep?

00:25.800 --> 00:27.800
Uncle Charlie and I
both had dreams about eating.

00:27.800 --> 00:30.000
Mine was with donuts.
His was something dirty.

00:31.500 --> 00:33.100
He's just guessing.

00:33.900 --> 00:35.200
Good guess.

00:36.300 --> 00:38.500
And yes, Alan, we
see your earring.

00:39.700 --> 00:40.800
It's pretty cool, right?

00:40.800 --> 00:44.000
Yeah, if you're going to a Wham!
concert with Molly Ringwald.

00:46.700 --> 00:48.600
I think it's cool.
Thank you, Jake.

00:48.600 --> 00:50.800
<i>Can I get my ear pierced?
No.</i>

00:50.800 --> 00:51.600
Why not?

00:51.600 --> 00:54.100
You can't keep
the holes you have clean.

00:55.300 --> 00:56.500
And you're too young.

00:56.700 --> 00:58.200
Wait till you're old, desperate,

00:58.200 --> 01:00.000
and living
in your brother's house.

01:00.500 --> 01:01.600
You can mock me all you want,

01:01.600 --> 01:04.099
but there's a certain lady
who thinks it's darn sexy.

01:04.099 --> 01:06.600
First of all, I don't need
permission to mock you...

01:07.200 --> 01:08.300
but more importantly,

01:08.300 --> 01:11.200
you let some broad talk you
into piercing your ear?

01:11.500 --> 01:14.500
Actually, my ear wasn't
her first choice to pierce.

01:16.700 --> 01:18.100
What else can you pierce?

01:20.700 --> 01:22.200
Nothing.
Nothing.

01:22.600 --> 01:23.700
Fine. Don't tell me.

01:23.700 --> 01:25.000
I'll Google it.

01:26.300 --> 01:27.100
Don't worry.

01:27.100 --> 01:28.800
He can't
spell "pierce."

01:29.700 --> 01:31.200
He can't spell "Google."

01:32.600 --> 01:35.500
So, who's Princess Poke-a-Hole?

01:36.100 --> 01:39.200
Just a nice young woman with
a sewing needle and a potato.

01:39.600 --> 01:40.700
A potato?

01:40.900 --> 01:42.600
Yeah, she, uh, she put it
behind my lobe,

01:42.600 --> 01:44.000
sort of like a pincushion.

01:44.000 --> 01:46.000
Oh. So you're a moron.

01:46.900 --> 01:48.000
It's perfectly safe.

01:48.000 --> 01:49.100
She sterilized the needle.

01:49.100 --> 01:50.000
How?

01:50.300 --> 01:51.500
With alcohol.

01:53.900 --> 01:55.200
Okay, Kahlua.

01:56.600 --> 01:59.000
Well, I guess I owe morons
an apology.

02:00.700 --> 02:02.900
You do know that's the gay ear.

02:08.000 --> 02:09.100
What?

02:10.100 --> 02:13.000
Left ear says "I'm a hipster
from the disco era."

02:13.000 --> 02:13.800
Right ear says...

02:13.800 --> 02:15.300
(flamboyantly):
"Let's disco!"

02:20.200 --> 02:21.500
No, no,
th-th-that can't be right.

02:21.500 --> 02:23.200
Okay, don't believe me.

02:24.200 --> 02:26.900
Hey, look who's finally
out of the closet.

02:27.500 --> 02:37.500
www.1000fr.com present

02:39.500 --> 02:48.500
Capture:fadeout 
