02:49.000 --> 02:49.600
Berta.

02:49.600 --> 02:51.400
Yeah.
What are you doing?

02:51.800 --> 02:53.300
Making your bed.

02:54.300 --> 02:56.000
Well, I'd like
to take a nap.

02:56.300 --> 02:58.900
Hop in. You can spoon me,
but it ends there.

03:00.800 --> 03:01.800
Are you sick?

03:01.800 --> 03:04.000
Yeah, I'm sick.

03:04.300 --> 03:06.900
I'm sick of staying up all night
with a screaming baby

03:06.900 --> 03:10.900
while my daughter's out trolling
the waterfront for the father of her next one.

03:11.900 --> 03:13.400
Whoa, that's rough.

03:13.600 --> 03:16.300
Oh, don't feign interest
in my life, Charlie.

03:17.100 --> 03:19.200
Sorry, I, I, I see
a woman in my bed,

03:19.200 --> 03:21.100
I instinctively
start lying.

03:23.000 --> 03:24.800
Close the door on your way out.

03:25.500 --> 03:26.800
Okay.

03:32.100 --> 03:33.300
No.

03:33.300 --> 03:34.800
No, this is ridiculous.

03:35.900 --> 03:36.800
Berta.
Get out.

03:36.800 --> 03:37.900
Sleep tight.

03:43.300 --> 03:44.500
Hello? Ow!

03:46.900 --> 03:48.100
Uh, hello?

03:48.100 --> 03:49.600
Oh, oh, hi.

03:49.800 --> 03:51.900
Uh, no, no, it's, uh,
it's just a little tender.

03:52.200 --> 03:54.200
I'm glad you called.
I, I missed you, too.

03:54.800 --> 03:56.400
Yeah, yeah, last
night was fun.

03:57.700 --> 03:59.500
You won't believe
who's in my bed.

04:00.200 --> 04:01.100
Hang on.

04:01.400 --> 04:02.800
I never do...

04:04.200 --> 04:05.700
but I'm on the
phone right now.

04:06.400 --> 04:07.100
Ow!

04:07.100 --> 04:09.000
Ah... damn it.

04:09.200 --> 04:11.000
Uh, listen, how
about tonight?

04:11.400 --> 04:12.200
Oh, great, great.

04:12.200 --> 04:13.400
The usual place?

04:13.900 --> 04:14.900
All right, well,
see you then.

04:15.300 --> 04:17.000
(chuckles)
Okay. B-Bye.

04:18.100 --> 04:19.800
Berta's in my bed.

04:20.600 --> 04:22.100
Really?

04:22.100 --> 04:24.000
Couldn't you just pay her
in cash this week?

04:26.600 --> 04:27.800
Ow!

04:29.500 --> 04:31.700
There are some things
we don't joke about.

04:33.300 --> 04:34.400
Okay, so...

04:34.500 --> 04:36.100
why is Berta
in your bed?

04:37.100 --> 04:39.200
Apparently, her daughter's been
out partying every night

04:39.200 --> 04:40.800
and Berta's been stuck
with the baby.

04:40.800 --> 04:43.200
Oh, that's got to be rough.

04:44.200 --> 04:46.600
Don't feign interest
in her life, Alan.

04:47.500 --> 04:48.200
Sorry.

04:48.200 --> 04:50.400
Oh, hey, hey, listen,
can you watch Jake tonight?

04:50.400 --> 04:54.400
Why? You want to see if your
new lady friend can infect other parts of your body?

04:55.200 --> 04:58.100
It's not infected.A certain amount of swelling
is perfectly normal.

04:58.100 --> 04:59.200
Where'd it say that, Alan?

04:59.200 --> 05:00.300
On the potato?

05:05.100 --> 05:07.200
Are you at least going to
tell me who this woman is?

05:07.200 --> 05:08.500
It's nobody you know.

05:09.600 --> 05:11.800
Oh... so I know her.

05:13.100 --> 05:14.100
I didn't say that.

05:14.100 --> 05:15.400
You didn't have to.

05:16.100 --> 05:17.000
Now let's see.

05:17.500 --> 05:19.500
Who do I know that you'd
like to keep a secret?

05:19.500 --> 05:20.600
You're wasting your time.

05:20.800 --> 05:22.100
One of your ex-wives?

05:22.700 --> 05:24.800
Rose? Berta's
daughter?

05:25.000 --> 05:26.500
(laughing):
Berta's daughter?

05:29.200 --> 05:31.200
D-Don't be ridiculous.

05:31.200 --> 05:33.300
Ha... ha-ha.

05:36.200 --> 05:37.600
That's rich.

05:38.500 --> 05:40.000
Ha, ha, ha!

05:42.100 --> 05:43.600
* Men... *

05:44.600 --> 05:46.600
I'm tired.
Shouldn't I be in bed?

05:46.600 --> 05:48.200
Shut up and deal.

05:48.900 --> 05:51.400
Look, I'll give you back
the money I won.

05:51.400 --> 05:53.200
You didn't win it
till we stop playing.

05:53.200 --> 05:55.000
Now deal.

05:56.800 --> 05:57.700
What's he doing up?

05:57.700 --> 05:58.800
Not now, Alan.

05:59.600 --> 06:00.700
I'm all in.

06:02.000 --> 06:03.200
Jake, bed.

06:03.200 --> 06:05.000
Hold on, Dad. Call ya.

06:05.400 --> 06:06.600
Pocket aces.

06:06.900 --> 06:07.800
What do you got?

06:07.800 --> 06:09.700
You heard your father.
Go to bed.

06:11.300 --> 06:13.000
He's been betting
on garbage all night.

06:15.000 --> 06:16.800
You let a 12-year-old
beat you at poker?

06:17.500 --> 06:18.900
He's 12 and a half.

06:20.900 --> 06:22.800
What's going on
with your ear, Dumbo?

06:23.500 --> 06:24.900
It's just a little swelling.

06:24.900 --> 06:25.900
It's normal.

06:26.700 --> 06:29.700
You don't want to be
flying around in circles.

06:31.100 --> 06:32.400
It's fine.

06:32.400 --> 06:34.600
Listen, th-there's something
I need to get off my chest.

06:34.800 --> 06:37.600
If you don't see
a doctor soon,it'll be your earlobe.

06:38.300 --> 06:40.100
Are you going
to listen or what?
Sorry.

06:40.100 --> 06:42.500
I'm all ears.
No, wait, that's you.

06:43.500 --> 06:44.300
You know what? Forget about it.

06:44.300 --> 06:46.200
No, no, no, no,
come on. Talk to me.
(sighs)

06:47.100 --> 06:48.300
It's about the girl I'm dating.

06:48.300 --> 06:49.300
Berta's daughter.

06:50.200 --> 06:51.400
How didyou know?

06:52.100 --> 06:54.100
Your idiot son doesn't
have a single tell,

06:54.200 --> 06:56.200
but you I can read
like a stop sign.

06:57.200 --> 06:58.000
Okay.

06:58.600 --> 07:00.600
I was going to build up
to the big reveal, but I...

07:00.600 --> 07:02.400
Just cut to the chase.

07:03.500 --> 07:06.600
You remember how I had
a little crush on Naomi when she was pregnant?

07:06.600 --> 07:07.600
A little crush?

07:07.800 --> 07:10.100
You were like a monkey
trying to hump a watermelon.

07:11.300 --> 07:12.700
Are you going
to let me tell the story?

07:12.900 --> 07:14.400
I'm just fact-checking.

07:14.600 --> 07:15.200
Go ahead.

07:15.200 --> 07:19.200
Anyway, after she had the baby,
we stayed in touch,

07:19.200 --> 07:21.400
and I got to know her
and the baby and...

07:22.100 --> 07:23.800
I'm starting to care
about both of them.

07:23.800 --> 07:26.800
Aw, buddy, you got a heart
as big as your ear.

07:29.300 --> 07:31.700
But you're falling into
the same trap you always do.

07:31.700 --> 07:32.600
What's that?

07:32.800 --> 07:34.700
You're a pathological
rescuer.

07:35.100 --> 07:36.200
Ever since you're
a little kid,

07:36.200 --> 07:38.500
bringing home that
stray three-legged cat.

07:38.900 --> 07:40.000
Oh, yeah, Tippy.

07:41.000 --> 07:43.000
And finding the
sick baby bird...

07:43.000 --> 07:45.500
Mm.
...feeding it with
an eyedropper,nursing it back to health.

07:45.500 --> 07:47.000
Until Tippy ate it.

07:48.000 --> 07:50.100
And it's the same
thing with women.

07:50.100 --> 07:53.800
You constantly seek out
these damaged, needy broads.

07:54.200 --> 07:55.900
You know, you're right.

07:55.900 --> 07:57.500
Maybe subconsciously
I'm hoping

07:57.500 --> 07:59.500
that if I save them,
they'll love me.

07:59.500 --> 08:00.600
Perhaps.

08:00.600 --> 08:03.000
Or subconsciously you realize
the only way

08:03.000 --> 08:04.700
an emotionally healthy,
self-supporting woman

08:04.700 --> 08:06.800
would pick you up is
on a scavenger hunt.

08:08.300 --> 08:10.400
But... we digress.

08:11.000 --> 08:14.100
Please continue with
your star-crossed love story.

08:14.100 --> 08:17.500
Well, Naomi and I
have been sneaking around behind Berta's back

08:17.500 --> 08:18.400
and...

08:18.400 --> 08:19.900
I'm starting
to feel guilty about it.

08:20.000 --> 08:21.200
You want my advice?

08:21.300 --> 08:24.500
Live with the guilt
and see a doctor before that thing
grows teeth.

08:25.800 --> 08:28.400
But don't you think
the honorable thing would be to tell Berta?

08:28.600 --> 08:30.400
Sure, honorable's one way to go.

08:31.100 --> 08:35.100
But may I remind you that
this is a woman who's been known to lift the stove with one hand

08:35.500 --> 08:38.100
in order to beat a mouse
to death with the other.

08:40.600 --> 08:42.700
How much honor you think
that little fella had?

08:43.400 --> 08:45.200
Oh... now you're
just being silly.

08:45.200 --> 08:47.700
I mean, Berta's not going
to physically assault me.

08:48.100 --> 08:49.300
I hope you're right.

08:50.900 --> 08:53.500
I've grown to enjoy
these little talks.

08:56.400 --> 08:57.900
* Men... *

08:58.600 --> 09:00.700
Why don't you just pay me
what you owe me?

09:01.800 --> 09:03.600
I don't owe you till we're done.

09:05.300 --> 09:07.100
Now throw the dice.

09:09.900 --> 09:11.400
Oh, you just suck.

09:13.400 --> 09:15.900
I wouldn't need a job
if I joined the Army.

09:15.900 --> 09:18.400
You can't join
the Army.
Why not?

09:18.500 --> 09:21.100
Because you already are
all that you can be.

09:21.700 --> 09:24.900
You remember
my little burden Naomi.

09:24.900 --> 09:27.500
Oh, sure, I remember her.
Hi.

09:27.900 --> 09:29.700
She's got job
interviews
this afternoon.

09:29.700 --> 09:31.300
I'm gonna watch the baby.

09:31.600 --> 09:33.300
<i>How are you going to work
and watch the baby?</i>

09:33.300 --> 09:35.000
Who said I was gonna work?

09:37.100 --> 09:38.100
CHARLIE:
Hey, Alan.

09:38.500 --> 09:39.900
Look who's here.

09:41.600 --> 09:43.600
Oh. H-Hello.
Hi.

09:43.600 --> 09:45.500
Um... Nancy, right?

09:45.500 --> 09:48.000
Uh, Naomi.
Naomi. Naomi, sure.

09:48.500 --> 09:49.300
(chuckling):
Been a long time.

09:49.300 --> 09:50.700
Sure has.

09:51.100 --> 09:52.200
And this must be
your baby.

09:52.200 --> 09:53.600
Oh, isn't she cute?

09:53.600 --> 09:55.000
Oh, thanks.

09:55.000 --> 09:56.800
And there's
the proud grandma.

09:57.100 --> 09:58.700
Look at her beaming.

09:59.800 --> 10:02.800
Well, dip me in butter
and roll me in nuts.

10:04.500 --> 10:06.800
I, too, am shocked.

10:08.100 --> 10:09.600
So you're the
sleazeball

10:09.600 --> 10:11.100
she's been running
around with.

10:11.100 --> 10:13.600
Oh, Alan, how could you?

10:14.500 --> 10:15.800
I-It's my fault, Mom.

10:15.800 --> 10:16.900
Alan wanted to tell you.

10:16.900 --> 10:18.800
No, no, it's,
it's my responsibility.

10:18.800 --> 10:21.300
If you're gonna do anything,
do it to me.

10:28.000 --> 10:30.500
???

10:36.900 --> 10:40.900
????

10:41.400 --> 10:43.200
I made you breakfast.

10:44.000 --> 10:44.600
Really?

10:44.600 --> 10:46.500
Need to have your morning
tinkle first?

10:48.600 --> 10:50.000
No, I'm okay.

10:50.600 --> 10:51.200
Good.

10:51.200 --> 10:52.700
I made all
your favorites:

10:52.900 --> 10:55.100
scrambled egg whites,
turkey bacon,

10:55.100 --> 10:57.900
rye toast no butter,
decaf coffee.

10:58.400 --> 10:59.500
Well, thank you.

10:59.600 --> 11:02.800
You eat like a 90-year-old
man with stomach cancer,but I don't judge.

11:05.600 --> 11:06.300
So...

11:06.600 --> 11:09.100
what do you and my little girl
have planned for today?

11:09.300 --> 11:11.600
Maybe a romantic
walk on the beach?

11:11.700 --> 11:12.600
A cozy picnic?

11:12.600 --> 11:14.100
I could pack you a lunch.

11:14.200 --> 11:15.600
Uh, gee, Berta, I don't...

11:15.600 --> 11:16.600
Or how about this?

11:16.800 --> 11:18.000
I'll watch the baby

11:18.000 --> 11:20.900
and you two can spend the
afternoon in bed gettin' sticky.

11:22.700 --> 11:25.800
Ah, well, uh, as lovely
as that sounds,

11:26.100 --> 11:28.800
I wasn't really planning
on seeing Naomi today.

11:28.900 --> 11:30.700
Why not? What's wrong?

11:30.700 --> 11:32.800
Oh, please don't tell me
there's something wrong.

11:33.000 --> 11:35.600
I mean, you ain't much, but
you're the best she ever had.

11:37.200 --> 11:38.700
No, no, nothing's wrong.

11:38.700 --> 11:39.600
I just...

11:39.700 --> 11:41.000
I have to go
to work today.

11:41.200 --> 11:42.900
Oh, right.

11:42.900 --> 11:43.900
Silly me.

11:44.300 --> 11:47.900
Naomi never dated anybody
with a job before.

11:48.700 --> 11:50.900
At least not one
that's indoors and legal.

11:52.000 --> 11:53.200
I understand.

11:53.500 --> 11:55.400
Well, you let me know
if you need anything.

11:55.400 --> 11:56.300
I will.

11:56.400 --> 11:57.700
Ironing, groceries?

11:57.700 --> 11:59.300
I could lance that ear for you.

12:00.400 --> 12:01.600
Uh, no, thanks.

12:02.000 --> 12:03.000
I know what I'm doin'.

12:03.000 --> 12:05.400
I spent a summer castrating
sheep in Montana.

12:07.900 --> 12:09.300
I'll keep that in mind.

12:09.500 --> 12:11.000
Uh, but I think it's fine.

12:11.100 --> 12:12.200
Okay.

12:13.900 --> 12:16.700
You made an old lady
very happy, Alan.

12:18.000 --> 12:18.900
I'm...

12:19.800 --> 12:21.000
glad.

12:23.400 --> 12:24.600
Bye-bye now.

12:25.300 --> 12:26.300
Bye-bye.

12:30.500 --> 12:32.400
Oh, I am so screwed.

12:34.300 --> 12:35.200
Charlie?

12:35.600 --> 12:36.900
I'm in the bathroom,
Alan.

12:37.800 --> 12:38.500
Um...

12:38.800 --> 12:40.900
I've got kind
of a delicate problem.

12:41.300 --> 12:43.500
The antibiotics are
in my dresser drawer.

12:44.800 --> 12:45.900
(toilet flushing)
No, no, it's, it's Berta.

12:45.900 --> 12:47.400
She's being ridiculously nice
to me

12:47.400 --> 12:50.300
and I'm afraid what might happen
if I break up with her daughter.

12:51.000 --> 12:53.000
Oh, you can't break up
with her daughter.

12:53.500 --> 12:54.900
Whaddya mean I can't break up
with her?

12:56.200 --> 12:58.300
Well, I guess
you could, but...

13:01.100 --> 13:02.500
So what am I
supposed to do,

13:02.500 --> 13:04.900
marry Naomi just
to keep Berta happy?

13:05.200 --> 13:06.700
You don't have
to marry her.

13:06.700 --> 13:09.200
Just let the relationship
follow its natural course.

13:09.400 --> 13:10.300
Natural course?

13:11.100 --> 13:12.200
Think about it, Alan.

13:12.200 --> 13:16.200
Any woman, given enough time,
will grow to loathe you.

13:18.600 --> 13:19.900
My God, you're right.

13:21.200 --> 13:23.000
So I just have to stick it out
with Naomi

13:23.000 --> 13:24.300
until she hates my guts.

13:24.300 --> 13:25.600
How long could it take?

13:27.200 --> 13:30.300
BERTA:
Damn it.Charlie, get your lazy ass out
of that bed.

13:31.100 --> 13:32.700
Hello, bright eyes.

13:34.000 --> 13:34.800
Hi.

13:35.000 --> 13:37.000
I bagged you a lunch
to take to work.

13:37.200 --> 13:38.000
No kidding.

13:38.000 --> 13:38.900
Yeah.

13:39.000 --> 13:41.100
I also tossed in a
packet of vitamin E.

13:41.100 --> 13:44.000
Help you chalk up the
old pool cue for Naomi.

13:45.800 --> 13:46.500
Thanks.

13:46.500 --> 13:48.300
C'mere, gimme some sugar.

13:48.300 --> 13:49.400
Mwah.

13:55.200 --> 13:57.600
Oh, you are so screwed.

14:01.200 --> 14:02.100
Here you go.

14:02.300 --> 14:05.100
One hot chocolate
for the lactating mommy.

14:05.100 --> 14:06.100
Thank you.

14:06.800 --> 14:09.700
I see little Brittany Pam
is having the grande boobaccino.

14:09.700 --> 14:10.500
Yeah,

14:10.700 --> 14:12.400
and she's bitin' the straw.

14:14.700 --> 14:16.600
Listen, you got any plans
for Saturday night?

14:16.700 --> 14:17.900
I don't think so. Why?

14:18.100 --> 14:21.300
Well, my mom wants to have a big
family dinner over at her place.

14:22.100 --> 14:22.900
Family?

14:23.100 --> 14:24.100
Uh, whose family?

